info.senderName: NWS Duluth (Northeast Minnesota and Northern Wisconsin)
info.headline: Flood Advisory issued September 12 at 1:03AM CDT by NWS Duluth
info.description: ...FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM CDT EARLY THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected. * WHERE...St. Louis County. * WHEN...Until 500 AM CDT Tuesday. * IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. River or stream flows are elevated. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1259 AM CDT Tuesday, trained weather spotters reported heavy rain and flooding in the advisory area earlier this evening due to thunderstorms. This has caused urban and small stream flooding. Between 3 and 5 inches of rain have fallen. - Heavy rainfall has fallen over the Chester Creek basin and Central Hillside neighborhoods. Small streams and creeks are elevated and flowing fast. Use caution around waterways. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... City of Rice Lake, East Hillside, Chester Park, Central Hillside, Kenwood, Congdon Park. - Flood safety information can be found at www.weather.gov/safety/flood.
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
